  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money seem legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most involve intentionally disguising the origin of money obtained through criminal activities.",
